SUMMARY:Seeds | InLight Human Rights Documentary Film Festival
DESCRIPTION:Filmed over nine years in black-and-white\, Seeds intimately 
 portrays Black farmers in the American South fighting to preserve their a
 ncestral lands amid economic injustices and dwindling subsidies. Director
  Brittany Shyne follows enduring families like the Williams siblings and 
 activist Willie Head Jr. Seeds captures daily labor\, community bonds\, a
 nd activism against systemic barriers.&#160\;
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<p>  Filmed over nine years in black-and-whi
 te\, Seeds intimately portrays Black farmers in the American South fighti
 ng to preserve their ancestral lands amid economic injustices and dwindli
 ng subsidies. Director Brittany Shyne follows enduring families like the 
 Williams siblings and activist Willie Head Jr. Seeds captures daily labor
 \, community bonds\, and activism against systemic barriers.&#160\;</p>
