SUMMARY:Franklin Jazz Hall Performance by Tortilla Jackson
DESCRIPTION:Tortilla Jackson is a high-energy Latin jazz and funk ensembl
 e known for their playful improvisation and genre-blending sound. With ro
 ots in Bloomington's vibrant music scene\, the group brings a fresh take 
 to the music of Willie Bobo\, Mongo Santamaría\, James Brown\, and other
 s.&#160\;  Hosted by WFIU's David Brent Johnson\, this event is hosted by
  The Media School and Indiana Public Media.
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<p>  Tortilla Jackson is a high-energy Latin
  jazz and funk ensemble known for their playful improvisation and genre-b
 lending sound. With roots in Bloomington's vibrant music scene\, the grou
 p brings a fresh take to the music of Willie Bobo\, Mongo Santamaría\, J
 ames Brown\, and others.&#160\;</p><p>  Hosted by WFIU's David Brent John
 son\, this event is hosted by The Media School and Indiana Public Media.<
