SUMMARY:Slumlord Millionaire | InLight Human Rights Documentary Film Fest
 ival
DESCRIPTION:Exposing the corruption behind New York City's gentrification
  issues\, Slumlord Millionaire follows tenants and activists in their fig
 ht against landlords. This documentary by directors Steph Ching and Ellen
  Martinez explores the relationship between local politicians\, the judic
 iary system\, and real estate\, revealing the systemic relationships that
  have facilitated the housing crisis.
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<p>  Exposing the corruption behind New York
  City's gentrification issues\, Slumlord Millionaire follows tenants and 
 activists in their fight against landlords. This documentary by directors
  Steph Ching and Ellen Martinez explores the relationship between local p
 oliticians\, the judiciary system\, and real estate\, revealing the syste
 mic relationships that have facilitated the housing crisis.</p>
