DTSTART:20260415T123000Z
DTEND:20260415T133000Z
LOCATION:OWEN HALL - Room Number: Wells Conference Room (1st FL)
GEO:39.166975;-86.523838
SUMMARY:College Luminary Breakfast with Entrepreneur and IU Alumna Erica 
 Anderson\, B.A.J. '06
DESCRIPTION:Open to all IU College of Arts + Sciences students\, join alu
 mna Erica Anderson\, B.A.J. '06\, an entrepreneur whose career spans Twit
 ter\, Google\, CBS News\, MTV News\, and Vox Media\, and who is now the c
 o-founder and CEO of The New Savant\, for an informal breakfast on Wednes
 day\, April 15 at 8:30 a.m.  As one of Twitter's first 300 employees\, Er
 ica helped launch the platform's early journalism program and later led g
 lobal efforts at Google to strengthen the news ecosystem. Today she is bu
 ilding a scent company that has generated millions in organic sales by fi
 nding product market fit and building community outside the traditional s
 tartup playbook.In a moment when rapid technological change is reshaping 
 how we work and create\, Erica will share insights on curiosity\, creativ
 e courage\, and building meaningful work in a world where careers are evo
 lving faster than ever. Drawing from her experience across media\, techno
 logy\, and entrepreneurship\, she will discuss how to follow emerging ide
 as\, trust your internal compass\, and build opportunities even when the 
 path forward is uncertain.Students will learn how to:Identify emerging op
 portunities and build careers that did not previously exist  Stay grounde
 d in personal values and curiosity in a world where work is constantly ev
 aluated and changing  Navigate uncertainty in the age of AI while creatin
 g meaningful work and community  Bagels and coffee provided. Registration
  is requested as space is limited.
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<p>  Open to all IU College of Arts + Scienc
 es students\, join alumna Erica Anderson\, B.A.J. '06\, an entrepreneur <
 strong>whose career spans Twitter\, Google\, CBS News\, MTV News\, and Vo
 x Media</strong>\, and who is now the <strong>co-founder and CEO of The N
 ew Savant</strong>\, for an informal breakfast on Wednesday\, April 15 at
  8:30 a.m.</p><p>  As one of Twitter's first 300 employees\, Erica helped
  launch the platform's early journalism program and later led global effo
 rts at Google to strengthen the news ecosystem. Today she is building a s
 cent company that has generated millions in organic sales by finding prod
 uct market fit and building community outside the traditional startup pla
 ybook.</p><p><strong>In a moment when rapid technological change</strong>
  is reshaping how we work and create\, Erica will <strong>share insights 
 on curiosity\, creative courage\, and building meaningful work</strong> i
 n a world where careers are evolving faster than ever. Drawing from her e
 xperience across media\, technology\, and entrepreneurship\, she will dis
 cuss how to follow emerging ideas\, trust your internal compass\, and bui
 ld opportunities even when the path forward is uncertain.</p><p><strong>S
 tudents will learn how to:</strong></p><ul><li>Identify emerging opportun
 ities and build careers that did not previously exist  </li><li>Stay grou
 nded in personal values and curiosity in a world where work is constantly
  evaluated and changing  </li><li>Navigate uncertainty in the age of AI w
 hile creating meaningful work and community  </li></ul><p><strong>Bagels 
 and coffee provided. Registration is requested as space is limited.</stro
 ng></p>
