X-SOURCE:IU Media School
DTSTART:20260417T230000Z
DTEND:20260418T000000Z
LOCATION:IU CINEMA
GEO:39.168613;-86.517376
SUMMARY:Montage Film Festival 2026 | Additional Films and Guests
DESCRIPTION:The Seventh Annual Montage Film Festival is IU's yearly celeb
 ration of student-produced films. Submitted films are viewed and judged b
 y IU alumni and awarded in several categories\, including Best in Show\, 
 Best Cinematography\, and Best Acting or Performance. Montage is a collab
 oration between IU Cinema and The Media School.  The collective runtime o
 f the films is 90 minutes.Bonnie and Clyde (4 min) | Directed by Olivia K
 inoshita  A lesbian Bonnie and Clyde\, three vignettes follow their seemi
 ngly mundane daily life: grocery shopping and cooking\, gardening\, and p
 eaceful drives. Each short feels like a romance until the chilling twist 
 reveals they are murderers\, turning each vignette into a thriller.  &#16
 0\;Kansas (7 min) | Directed by Goodman Murphy-Smith  Diary entries proce
 ssing escalating grief are read aloud to a montage of still frames.  &#16
 0\;Escape (10 min) | Directed by Noah Sanchez  A fading romantic comes ac
 ross an intriguing newspaper ad from a woman looking to escape a washed-o
 ut marriage.  &#160\;Cascade (4 min) | Directed by Dmitry N. Aslanov-Ohle
 r  A man struck with grief gives in to temptation and loses his mind. Con
 tains substance use.  &#160\;Allure (10 min) | Directed by Dylan Dankel  
 Following an onstage meltdown\, one  young guitarist must confront his ba
 ndmates as they demand answers\, all the while contemplating his relation
 ship with each of them. Contains substance use.  &#160\;Just Penelope Ban
 d Doc (7 min) | Directed by Betzabeth Leija-Castaneda  Through rehearsals
  and live sets\, this documentary short follows Just Penelope\, an up-and
 -coming local noise rock band\, off and on stage\, revealing the creative
  friction\, shared obsession\, and unspoken chemistry that fuel their unc
 ompromising sound.  &#160\;BL1NK (11 min) | Directed by Alex Ruppert  A y
 oung boy struggles to grieve the loss of his mother\, but finds guidance 
 in an AI friend instead of his father.  &#160\;Pesticide (4 min) | Direct
 ed by Gavin Baldwin  A boy has an eye-opening conversation with a wise ol
 d cockroach.  &#160\;Racket Abuse (10 min) | Directed by Gracie Runge  A 
 friendly college tennis match takes a destructive turn once tension arise
 s.  &#160\;Lookout (4 min) | Directed by Danny William  A detective hunts
  for a missing girl.  &#160\;Debt of Blood (13 min) | Directed by Marissa
  Baker  Set during the crack epidemic of the 1980s\, a young woman strugg
 ling with addiction uncovers a buried truth about her past and her closes
 t friend. Contains substance use and violence.  &#160\;Cogito\, ergo sum 
 (6 min) | Directed by Ahmed Tahsin Shams  When clay speaks\, history list
 ens. Cogito\, ergo sum is a hybrid documentary that fuses the real-life r
 eflections of ceramicist Malcolm Mobutu Smith with a claymation resurrect
 ion of two long-erased Black comic characters—Whitewash Jones and Li'L 
 Tuffy—who return to confront their origins\, reclaim their stories\, an
 d ask\, "Who's holding the pen now?"
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<p>  The Seventh Annual Montage Film Festiva
 l is IU's yearly celebration of student-produced films. Submitted films a
 re viewed and judged by IU alumni and awarded in several categories\, inc
 luding Best in Show\, Best Cinematography\, and Best Acting or Performanc
 e. Montage is a collaboration between IU Cinema and The Media School.</p>
 <p>  The collective runtime of the films is 90 minutes.</p><p><strong>Bon
 nie and Clyde</strong> (4 min) | Directed by Olivia Kinoshita</p><p>  A l
 esbian Bonnie and Clyde\, three vignettes follow their seemingly mundane 
 daily life: grocery shopping and cooking\, gardening\, and peaceful drive
 s. Each short feels like a romance until the chilling twist reveals they 
 are murderers\, turning each vignette into a thriller.</p><p>  &#160\;</p
 ><p><strong>Kansas</strong> (7 min) | Directed by Goodman Murphy-Smith</p
 ><p>  Diary entries processing escalating grief are read aloud to a monta
 ge of still frames.</p><p>  &#160\;</p><p><strong>Escape</strong> (10 min
 ) | Directed by Noah Sanchez</p><p>  A fading romantic comes across an in
 triguing newspaper ad from a woman looking to escape a washed-out marriag
 e.</p><p>  &#160\;</p><p><strong>Cascade</strong> (4 min) | Directed by D
 mitry N. Aslanov-Ohler</p><p>  A man struck with grief gives in to tempta
 tion and loses his mind. <i>Contains substance use.</i></p><p>  &#160\;</
 p><p><strong>Allure</strong> (10 min) | Directed by Dylan Dankel</p><p>  
 Following an onstage meltdown\, one<br />  young guitarist must confront 
 his bandmates as they demand answers\, all the while contemplating his re
 lationship with each of them. <i>Contains substance use.</i></p><p>  &#16
 0\;</p><p><strong>Just Penelope Band Doc</strong> (7 min) | Directed by B
 etzabeth Leija-Castaneda</p><p>  Through rehearsals and live sets\, this 
 documentary short follows Just Penelope\, an up-and-coming local noise ro
 ck band\, off and on stage\, revealing the creative friction\, shared obs
 ession\, and unspoken chemistry that fuel their uncompromising sound.</p>
 <p>  &#160\;</p><p><strong>BL1NK</strong> (11 min) | Directed by Alex Rup
 pert</p><p>  A young boy struggles to grieve the loss of his mother\, but
  finds guidance in an AI friend instead of his father.</p><p>  &#160\;</p
 ><p><strong>Pesticide</strong> (4 min) | Directed by Gavin Baldwin</p><p>
   A boy has an eye-opening conversation with a wise old cockroach.</p><p>
   &#160\;</p><p><strong>Racket Abuse</strong> (10 min) | Directed by Grac
 ie Runge</p><p>  A friendly college tennis match takes a destructive turn
  once tension arises.</p><p>  &#160\;</p><p><strong>Lookout</strong> (4 m
 in) | Directed by Danny William</p><p>  A detective hunts for a missing g
 irl.</p><p>  &#160\;</p><p><strong>Debt of Blood</strong> (13 min) | Dire
 cted by Marissa Baker</p><p>  Set during the crack epidemic of the 1980s\
 , a young woman struggling with addiction uncovers a buried truth about h
 er past and her closest friend. <i>Contains substance use and violence.</
 i></p><p>  &#160\;</p><p><strong>Cogito\, ergo sum</strong> (6 min) | Dir
 ected by Ahmed Tahsin Shams</p><p>  When clay speaks\, history listens. <
 i>Cogito\, ergo sum</i> is a hybrid documentary that fuses the real-life 
 reflections of ceramicist Malcolm Mobutu Smith with a claymation resurrec
 tion of two long-erased Black comic characters—Whitewash Jones and Li'L
  Tuffy—who return to confront their origins\, reclaim their stories\, a
 nd ask\, "Who's holding the pen now?"</p>
